  "title": "Senior Executive, Corporate Communications",
  "description": "<ul><li>Support the planning and execution of corporate communication strategies that align with the firm’s overall objectives.</li><li>Provide communications guidance to internal stakeholders to ensure message consistency and alignment across all channels.</li><li>Manage the firm’s awards programme, including coordinating timelines and preparing submissions.</li><li>Draft, edit, and proofread corporate materials such as publications, award entries, media releases, web articles, and EDMs.      </li><li>Maintain and update the company website, social media platforms, and intranet with accurate, engaging, and timely content.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in a relevant business or marketing discipline</li><li>At least 1-3 years of experience; ideal industry to be from built-environment.</li><li>Demonstrate expertise in design and hand-drawing with the ability to consistently meet project timelines.</li></ul><p>If this opportunity aligns with your skills and experience, please submit your resume to <a href=\"mailto:koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></a></p><p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p><p>www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
